Defendant Jordan K Johnson in court with attorney Bridget Joy Krause.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  To the charged offense:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms/body armor.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.   
Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing. Court sentenced the defendant to serve 12 months in the House of Correction; credit for 12 days served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 18 MONTHS with the following conditions:
-Follow all rules of probation.
-No further violations of the law.
-AODA assessment and any treatment.
-Absolute sobriety.
-Random urine screens.
-No driving unless validly licensed.
-Maintain employment and/or school on a full-time basis.
-Other counseling needs to be determined.
-Perform 60 HOURS of community service at a non-profit agency.
-Pay victim witness surcharge and all costs, assessments and surcharges.
-Provide for DNA sample and pay costs; DNA surcharge
FAILURE TO PAY ALL FINANCIAL OBLIGATIONS WILL RESULT IN ENTRY OF CIVIL JUDGMENT.
As a convicted felon you may not carry or possess any firearms or body armor and your civil rights are suspended until they are restored.
Upon completion of ALL TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF PROBATION the court will authorize expungment.
